President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Maine due to the COVID-19 pandemic. This declaration allows for federal assistance to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts. Federal funding is available for emergency protective measures, including direct federal assistance, for all areas in Maine impacted by COVID-19. W. Russell Webster has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further assessments. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.